reviewText: Great movies of my youth. It keeps it alive.
This is a fun video especially if you had enjoyed watching them years ago on TV. It brings back great moments in westerns.

As you can easily see below, lots of great actors appeared in TV westerns back in the 1950s and '60s, both on a regular basis and as guest stars. The 50 GREAT WESTERN TV SHOWS box set is a fine way for us old folks to remember the westerns we loved as kids, and an even better opportunity for later generations to experience some of television's greatest vintage programming. If this fine BRENTWOOD product is to your liking, then the ULTIMATE TV WESTERNS - 150 Episodes box set will knock you right outta yer boots! . The following list places the programs and episodes in alphabetical order. It also provides season and episode numbers, original airdates and guest stars. This list is from dvdtvshows.com, which has lots of TV on DVD at reasonable prices.  I ordered this set from Amazon as the price was lower, but I haven't received the set or watched it yet. I had to give it a rating in order to post this list.

50 Great Western TV Shows - 10 DVD Set - 2220 Minutes - 50 Episodes - DVD Street Release Date: February 3, 2004
